Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.66,0:00:04.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dear Mouri Kogorou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.30,0:00:07.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seeing you as a great detective, I have a request for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.22,0:00:12.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A crime of murder was placed upon me eleven years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.10,0:00:16.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please clear my name at all costs with your great deductions.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.65,0:00:21.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll give you the details at dawn on December 19th...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.24,0:00:25.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the Gunma prefecture, at Kuchibashi Village's\NKoura Inn, which is near the crime scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.49,0:00:28.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tatezato Mika.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.66,0:00:29.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.58,0:00:35.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This woman is a murderer on the run,\Nand she wants to meet with Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.54,0:00:37.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's probably the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.91,0:00:40.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Probably the case"?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.13,0:00:42.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you sure it's all right to meet her?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.05,0:00:43.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.34,0:00:45.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You should contact the police first...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.64,0:00:49.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought so too, and had Yamamura\Nfrom the Gunma police investigate it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.98,0:00:54.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it seems there weren't any murder\Ncases near that inn eleven years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.23,0:00:58.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that there isn't a fugitive named Tatezato Mika.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.74,0:01:04.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yamamura said it's probably a bad prank.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.12,0:01:07.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then why did we come?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.87,0:01:10.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did I have a choice?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.66,0:01:14.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since we had already eaten the retainer\Nfee that was sent along with the letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.17,0:01:16.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Already eaten"?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.34,0:01:19.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me the Chinese cuisine we had yesterday...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.05,0:01:21.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.63,0:01:25.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This old guy ended up ordering a lot of\Nexpensive-looking dishes and alcohol.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.09,0:01:30.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, we're only going to determine whether or not it's a prank.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.03,0:01:52.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we continue lamenting the passing seasons...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.83,0:01:54.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll be unable to confront the mysteries of cases!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.83,0:01:56.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Today marks our 600th episode!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.69,0:01:58.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The green legend and the kappa's curse!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.00,0:02:00.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perceiving the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.50,0:02:02.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The appearance of a child and the intellect of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.46,0:02:04.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is: Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.49,0:03:49.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.86,0:03:50.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was dangerous!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.99,0:03:52.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.12,0:03:55.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But are you going to Koura Inn by any chance?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.83,0:03:58.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we are...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.12,0:04:00.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, could you give me a ride?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.12,0:04:03.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm also staying there today.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.05,0:04:06.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fine, I don't mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.76,0:04:09.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.60,0:04:15.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whew, you saved me!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.93,0:04:18.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought I'd walk there from the station...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.81,0:04:20.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I started breathing hard midway.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.81,0:04:22.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You wouldn't happen to be Tatezato{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, would you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.41,0:04:24.42,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.46,0:04:27.36,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,My name is Tokubi Rokurou.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.41,0:04:28.04,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\blur2\be5\fad(210,210)}Tokubi Rokurou (42)\NPainter
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.95,0:04:36.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I think it's quite a long way from the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.12,0:04:41.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I taught at an elementary school near here a long time ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.25,0:04:46.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I liked to walk around and take in the scenery of this area, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.17,0:04:48.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It turns out I'm not as fit as I used to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.63,0:04:52.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, that school was shut down later...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.47,0:04:55.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I quit being a teacher and became a starving painter.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.10,0:04:57.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.41,0:05:02.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though you're already allowing me to ride with you, would\Nyou mind stopping somewhere so I can visit a gravesite?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.81,0:05:04.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A gravesite?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.65,0:05:12.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So one of the kids got swept away by the river and drowned?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.74,0:05:13.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.74,0:05:17.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one who died was a child named Numayama Tatsuhiko.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.45,0:05:20.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems he was swept away to a reservoir downstream.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.91,0:05:22.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was that...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.12,0:05:25.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The murder case that happened eleven years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.79,0:05:27.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wasn't a murder, but an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.67,0:05:33.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though it was raining hard, it seems he was\Nstill playing in the river and got swept away.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.63,0:05:36.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that was about ten years ago, I believe.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.18,0:05:40.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tokubi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.64,0:05:41.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.60,0:05:43.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it isn't Araiwa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.23,0:05:46.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you also came to visit the grave?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.19,0:05:47.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.13,0:05:50.72,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Today was the day of Tatsuhiko's death.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.53,0:05:51.19,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Araiwa Kazuki (21)\NTatsuhiko's Classmate
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.78,0:05:55.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But for a grave, this is pretty ill prepared.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.16,0:05:57.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, the real grave is somewhere else.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.28,0:06:03.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is what our classmates made when Tatsuhiko died.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.29,0:06:08.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Instead of his remains, we buried things\Nthat reminded us of Tatsuhiko.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.67,0:06:11.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, I also visited his real grave.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.01,0:06:14.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, why here?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.26,0:06:21.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was this river flowing behind me that\Nswept him away and killed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.85,0:06:24.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Exactly eleven years ago today.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.69,0:06:26.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eleven years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.73,0:06:30.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So the murder case mentioned in that letter was indeed...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.48,0:06:32.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Letter?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.15,0:06:35.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How did you know he was swept away by this river?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.49,0:06:40.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wasn't the child found in a reservoir downstream?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.53,0:06:42.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because his shoe was found.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.74,0:06:46.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tatsuhiko's shoe was caught between\Nthe rocks at the bottom of the river.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.08,0:06:53.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why Tatsuhiko likely got his foot caught between the rocks\Nwhile playing in the river, and couldn't manage to escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.38,0:06:58.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The rain started falling harder and harder, and the flood\Neventually swept him away, according to the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.30,0:07:04.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But to think he'd play in the river in December...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.22,0:07:06.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which part of the river was it again?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.48,0:07:09.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where his shoe was found...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.06,0:07:12.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was over where the rocks are sticking out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.52,0:07:14.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think it was right here...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.65,0:07:17.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that shoe still out there somewhere?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.65,0:07:19.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it was buried in that grave...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.99,0:07:21.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You could probably see it if you dug it up...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.62,0:07:27.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.21,0:07:27.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.29,0:07:30.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.42,0:07:31.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's shallow.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.80,0:07:38.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My art supplies seem to have survived somehow...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.63,0:07:42.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But this sketchbook isn't usable anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.39,0:07:46.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This incense is ruined as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.68,0:07:51.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My things were inside this vinyl bag, so they're pretty much dry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.44,0:07:55.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The caps of these plastic bottles were tightly closed...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.15,0:07:56.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And my pillow and change of clothes are safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.11,0:07:57.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,HEY!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.82,0:08:00.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you guys doing!?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.45,0:08:06.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Haven't I seen your faces somewhere before?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.12,0:08:10.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm Tatsuhiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s friend, and I came to pray at his grave...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.71,0:08:13.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Pray at his grave?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.63,0:08:16.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What kind of grave is this!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.20,0:08:18.56,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Listen up.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.62,0:08:21.01,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,My son died eleven years ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.18,0:08:21.01,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Numayama Banzou (51)\NTatsuhiko's Father
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.76,0:08:23.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just forget about it already!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.60,0:08:26.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Son?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.35,0:08:32.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So he was the deceased Tatsuhiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s father?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.81,0:08:33.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.94,0:08:37.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's also the owner of the inn we're all going to.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.69,0:08:42.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why was the owner of the inn at a place like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.78,0:08:44.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My guess is he was keeping watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.33,0:08:47.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Keeping watch?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.08,0:08:50.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That inn is on high ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.12,0:08:56.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems that if you use binoculars from the window\Nin the attic, you would have an extensive view.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.01,0:08:59.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not here?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.26,0:09:03.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's really no one named Tatezato Mika staying here?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.47,0:09:07.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But she promised to meet me here early tomorrow morning...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.93,0:09:09.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I don't see her name...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.02,0:09:13.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, have you ever heard about a murder\Ncase happening eleven years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.27,0:09:15.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.27,0:09:16.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Don't know"?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.44,0:09:17.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It did happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.46,0:09:21.09,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Furthermore...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.10,0:09:23.99,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,river imp\NThey said the culprit was a kappa!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.16,0:09:23.99,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\blur2\be5\fad(210,0)}Nohira Bousuke (45)\NGuest
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.16,0:09:25.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kappa!?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.36,0:09:27.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.95,0:09:32.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are a plethora of anecdotes about\Nthe kappa's existence around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.21,0:09:37.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Twelve or thirteen years ago, people even\Nsaid they had really seen the kappa...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.67,0:09:41.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,TV crews and magazine reporters even came for the scoop.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.55,0:09:45.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Immediately afterward, a kid drowned in the river...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.30,0:09:48.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,People began clamoring about it being the work of the kappa.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.85,0:09:52.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But after that, witness reports of the kappa plummeted...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.73,0:09:55.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now almost no one comes here at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.98,0:09:57.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold on.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.07,0:10:02.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The name from this letter, "Tatezato Mika"...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.78,0:10:08.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you split up the characters tate,\Nsato, mi, ka, and rearrange them...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.70,0:10:12.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't they form the characters for kappa!?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.75,0:10:15.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That must be it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.50,0:10:18.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The kappa wanted to have its name cleared...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.13,0:10:20.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So it called Dad, who's a detective, to come here!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.71,0:10:25.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everyone here is dancing around that stupid superstition!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.72,0:10:28.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you tell any more of those made-up ghost stories...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.14,0:10:31.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll have you leave this inn!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.39,0:10:35.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you really sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.44,0:10:38.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You dropped your cell phone next to that river?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.27,0:10:42.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When we were at the river, I got a message from Sonoko...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.40,0:10:45.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And when I was typing a reply, those two fell into the river.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.11,0:10:48.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So it probably was at that time...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.07,0:10:51.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can't we do this tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.08,0:10:54.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought about that too, but Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} said...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.08,0:11:01.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the battery dies, we won't hear the phone ring\Nwhen we call and probably won't find it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.30,0:11:05.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm almost certain it was around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.18,0:11:08.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's split up and search.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.43,0:11:13.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, are you calling it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.47,0:11:14.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.73,0:11:21.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.70,0:11:29.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.28,0:11:31.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's that sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.96,0:11:42.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, what's wrong!?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.50,0:11:45.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kappa!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.05,0:11:45.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.92,0:11:46.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kappa?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.97,0:11:52.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's nothing like that here!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.89,0:11:54.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was just there!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.93,0:11:57.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Standing in the middle of the river and looking this way...!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.77,0:12:03.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you found your cell phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.53,0:12:11.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn, it's starting to rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.66,0:12:12.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's head back.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.83,0:12:14.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.46,0:12:23.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You saw the kappa?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.38,0:12:25.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.38,0:12:28.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My daughter was saying that it was at the river last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.09,0:12:33.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I bet she must've mistaken a tree branch for it or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.14,0:12:34.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm telling you it was really there!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.39,0:12:39.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perhaps it was really a ghost...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.44,0:12:41.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ghost?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.40,0:12:43.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's stop this talk about the kappa here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.11,0:12:48.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Otherwise that man's gonna start yelling again.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.11,0:12:50.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Speak of the devil.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.61,0:12:54.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is terrible!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.53,0:12:56.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The owner is...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.29,0:13:02.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His body was lying on the floor of that gloomy attic...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.67,0:13:07.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As if possessed by the kappa, and\Ndragged to the bottom of the pond.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.80,0:13:11.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Covered in a rancid liquid that stung our noses...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.51,0:13:16.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And clutching his deceased son's belongings to his chest.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.40,0:13:24.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.52,0:13:25.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He drowned?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.90,0:13:28.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's what the coroner said.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.36,0:13:37.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Furthermore, judging from the composition of water\Non the victim and the water found inside his body...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.20,0:13:43.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He may have been drowned at some polluted\Npond first and then transported here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.25,0:13:46.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, there was that terrible smell.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.17,0:13:47.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.00,0:13:51.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it looks like the culprit brought that smelly water here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.59,0:13:55.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look, this water bucket...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.35,0:13:57.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It has the same smell.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.68,0:14:00.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.18,0:14:04.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit brought that smelly water here in the bucket...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.56,0:14:10.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And after they submerged Banzou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s\Nface into it and drowned him...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.23,0:14:12.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They splashed the water all over his body, so it seems.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.24,0:14:16.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, why was Banzou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} in a place like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.41,0:14:18.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems it was his daily routine.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.03,0:14:24.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Every morning after waking up, he'd come here\Nand keep watch over the river from the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.92,0:14:26.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what the people in the inn told me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.46,0:14:29.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Using those binoculars.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.88,0:14:31.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And why was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.01,0:14:37.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's probably because his son Tatsuhiko died\Nafter being swept away by the river.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.43,0:14:41.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, to make sure no one else met the same fate as Tatsuhiko...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.93,0:14:43.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He kept watch from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.94,0:14:45.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.52,0:14:49.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oho, I can certainly see everything!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.52,0:14:51.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.57,0:14:54.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it were for his son's sake...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.45,0:14:57.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He wouldn't kick over the grave that his son's friends made for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.20,0:15:01.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems it wasn't his first or second time doing that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.24,0:15:03.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's probably something there.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.41,0:15:06.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Near that river, that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.79,0:15:12.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems that, after everyone would fall asleep,\Nhe'd occasionally prowl around that area.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.63,0:15:16.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the only thing there is the grave his friends made.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.43,0:15:18.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Speaking of which...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.14,0:15:22.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The shoe next to the body belonged to Tatsuhiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.85,0:15:27.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But didn't you say it was buried at his grave?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.06,0:15:27.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.98,0:15:30.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then I wonder if the culprit dug it up?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.98,0:15:35.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, the one that was buried was his right\Nshoe that was caught in the rocks.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.90,0:15:38.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But this seems to be his left shoe.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.91,0:15:39.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.74,0:15:45.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't this the shoe Tatsuhiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} was wearing when he was\Nfound in the reservoir after he got swept away by the river?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.12,0:15:51.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you mean one of his shoes fell off,\Nand the other stayed on his foot?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.34,0:15:55.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, it seems he was only wearing\Nhis swim shorts when he was found.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.47,0:15:57.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Only swim shorts?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.09,0:15:59.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In such a cold season?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.05,0:16:03.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why he was likely trying out cold-weather swimming.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.72,0:16:05.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it, it's the reservoir!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.31,0:16:08.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The smelly water that was all over Banzou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s body...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.69,0:16:13.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was the smell of the reservoir Tatsuhiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} was found floating in!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.15,0:16:17.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That reservoir turned into an illegal trash-dumping site...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.57,0:16:24.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And from that outrageous stench and view,\Npeople in the village gave it a new name.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.08,0:16:27.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The kappa's dwelling...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.08,0:16:29.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Hell Swamp!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.21,0:16:32.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Hell Swamp!?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.38,0:16:35.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then this incident was indeed...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.92,0:16:39.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The work of the kappa, wasn't it!?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.97,0:16:42.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now look here, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.55,0:16:49.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In this scientific era where space travel is possible,\Nmonsters like the kappa don't exist!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.39,0:16:51.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.10,0:16:52.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Last night, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.90,0:16:58.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, can you tell me where that reservoir is?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.19,0:17:00.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's about ten kilometers downstream from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.57,0:17:03.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then I'll have forensics go there...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.82,0:17:08.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And compare that reservoir water to the water found with the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.66,0:17:12.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, I think you should search everyone's belongings.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.79,0:17:18.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because the culprit would attract attention if they used\Nthis bucket to bring the smelly water into this inn.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.51,0:17:20.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They'd be found out immediately due to the smell.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.76,0:17:21.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.38,0:17:27.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're saying that in order to transport the\Nwater, it had to be inside an airtight container.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.22,0:17:28.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Furthermore...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.52,0:17:33.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems like the stairs to the attic are behind the restrooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.98,0:17:39.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyone could go to the attic by pretending to go to the restroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.94,0:17:40.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.15,0:17:46.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone among us in this inn could've\Nbrought the smelly water here...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.41,0:17:47.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And committed the crime!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.37,0:17:49.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yamamura!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.45,0:17:51.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's the victim's estimated time of death?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.62,0:17:52.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.21,0:17:55.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.33,0:17:57.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Between 6:00 and 7:00 this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.14,0:17:59.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.34,0:18:02.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Check the alibis of everyone in this inn!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.93,0:18:08.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm going to go through the rooms of everyone who's\Nstaying here and look for any suspicious containers!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.43,0:18:09.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.10,0:18:14.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait, isn't that supposed to be my job?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.73,0:18:17.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I did get promoted to Inspector, after all...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.07,0:18:19.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.57,0:18:23.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My containers capable of housing\Nwater with an airtight seal are these.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.70,0:18:27.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The big bottles of colored ink are 60 milliliters each.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.83,0:18:33.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The small bottles look to be about 15 milliliters,\Nbut each of them is pretty much full of ink.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.29,0:18:41.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The white container is also about half full of paint,\Nso the only empty one is this water bottle.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.51,0:18:47.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you can't drown someone in merely 100 milliliters, huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.89,0:18:48.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You see?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.56,0:18:52.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And would there happen to be any containers you hid from us?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.27,0:18:55.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't think there are any.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.10,0:18:59.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yesterday, after falling in the river, he opened\Nup his luggage immediately and checked.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.94,0:19:01.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There weren't any containers besides these.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.82,0:19:06.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why so many art supplies?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.53,0:19:08.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said he's a painter.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.87,0:19:14.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He also said he used to be a teacher at the\Nelementary school that Tatsuhiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} attended.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.91,0:19:19.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why I'm staying here, since I was going\Nto burn incense at Tatsuhiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s altar.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.75,0:19:20.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.88,0:19:25.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the time of the crime between 6 AM and 7 AM,\Nwhere were you and what were you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.17,0:19:27.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was sleeping in my room...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.18,0:19:31.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Until the inn personnel finished preparing\Nbreakfast and came to wake me up.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.93,0:19:37.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, were you also going to Tatsuhiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s altar to burn incense?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.19,0:19:38.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.40,0:19:41.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Many of us used to come and do it...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.82,0:19:43.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But now it's just me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.44,0:19:47.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, where were you between 6 AM and 7 AM?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.70,0:19:52.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I woke up at 6:30 and took a morning bath.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.37,0:19:54.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although I was the only one there.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.16,0:20:01.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only things that could hold water are\Nthese two 500 milliliter plastic bottles, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.63,0:20:06.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One of them isn't opened yet, and the other is still half full.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.13,0:20:09.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.55,0:20:13.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's a water pillow.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.81,0:20:16.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You put water inside and expand it, making it a pillow.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.64,0:20:19.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Without this pillow, I can't fall asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.98,0:20:22.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, it's the water pillow!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.15,0:20:27.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You put the smelly water from the reservoir inside\Nof this and secretly transported it, didn't you!?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.74,0:20:31.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As proof of that, see how there's no water in here now!?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.91,0:20:35.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since I was about to leave, I let the water out when I took my bath!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.12,0:20:38.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's probably the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.37,0:20:43.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That person also opened his luggage\Nafter falling into the river, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.34,0:20:45.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That pillow was flat.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.88,0:20:50.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But he still could've snuck out later to bring the water here, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.84,0:20:53.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, that's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.27,0:20:59.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A camera, a tripod, an IC recorder, and a laptop...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.44,0:21:01.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.19,0:21:03.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A reportage writer.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.02,0:21:07.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I pursue local ghost stories from various places.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.86,0:21:10.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you came here because of the kappa tale?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.57,0:21:12.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.70,0:21:14.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I wasn't able to gather much material.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.49,0:21:18.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But this sure is rare nowadays.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.37,0:21:21.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Instead of a digital camera, you're using a standard film camera.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.87,0:21:24.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's because I used to be a cameraman.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.67,0:21:26.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I couldn't care less for digital things.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.76,0:21:32.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, with all of these film canisters you could've easily brought in...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.51,0:21:34.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The water in question!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.26,0:21:35.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, now!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.26,0:21:36.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't I tell you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.81,0:21:41.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From before 6 AM until 7 AM, I was on\Nthe phone with the editor-in-charge!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.31,0:21:43.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that a bit long?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.85,0:21:47.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Calling someone so early and talking for over an hour!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.02,0:21:51.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wasn't able to find enough material for the kappa\Nstory, so we were discussing what to do!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.07,0:21:54.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since the printing deadline is approaching, and my camera broke!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.41,0:21:56.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your camera broke?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.12,0:21:58.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It got soaked from the rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.83,0:22:01.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Last night when I was taking pictures outside, it suddenlyâ€”
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.67,0:22:08.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And you're saying you caught a cold because of that?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.59,0:22:12.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I had a small cold to begin with...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.09,0:22:13.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it ended up getting worse...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.60,0:22:21.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The malodorous water Numayama\NBanzou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was drowned in...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.52,0:22:26.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that was indeed from the reservoir\Nwhere Tatsuhiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s body was found...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.11,0:22:31.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We can assume this incident occurred\Nas a result of Tatsuhiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s death.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.95,0:22:37.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is the culprit's purpose for making\Nit seem like a curse from the kappa?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.46,0:24:01.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Again with the kappa?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.97,0:24:03.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I swear it was really there!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.91,0:24:09.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is obviously...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.90,0:24:11.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An alien!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.50,0:24:13.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.95,0:24:16.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you tightly filled it in small containers, huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.90,0:24:19.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Allow me to explain to you the truth behind this case.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.77,0:24:23.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the name of the Gunma Police's First Division Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.54,0:24:32.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.84,0:24:34.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Color Green
